                                                                                                 terms (i.e., the should/shall language) used for some recommendations and requirements do not
                                                                                                 apply outside the federal government. For federal government organizations, the terms should and
                                                                                                 shall have the following meaning in this document:
                                                                                                       1. shall: This term is used to indicate a requirement for U. S. Federal government
